Test file: src/game-of-life.spec.ts
Failing test: "should make a dead cell with exactly 3 live neighbors become alive (reproduction)"
Expected behavior: nextGeneration([[0,0],[1,0],[0,1]]) must contain [1,1] (dead cell with 3 live neighbors becomes alive)
Current error: expected [[0,0],[1,0],[0,1]] to deep equally contain [1,1]
Implementation file: src/game-of-life.ts

The implementation currently only handles survival (filters live cells). It needs to also handle reproduction:
- Find all dead cells neighboring at least one live cell (candidate cells)
- A dead cell with exactly 3 live neighbors becomes alive

Key insight: Dead neighbor cells to check are all unique neighbors of all live cells that are not themselves alive.

Current implementation:
```typescript
type Cell = [number, number];

const countLiveNeighbors = (cell: Cell, liveCells: Cell[]): number => {
  const [x, y] = cell;
  return liveCells.filter(([cx, cy]) =>
    Math.abs(cx - x) <= 1 && Math.abs(cy - y) <= 1 && (cx !== x || cy !== y)
  ).length;
};

const survives = (neighborCount: number): boolean =>
  neighborCount === 2 || neighborCount === 3;

export function nextGeneration(cells: Cell[]): Cell[] {
  return cells.filter((cell) => survives(countLiveNeighbors(cell, cells)));
}
```

